Hi all,

Tom Fiore wrote:

> Theorem. 9.17
> Let X and A be strict 2-categories, and G:A -> X a pseudo functor. Ther=
e
> exists a left biadjoint for G if and only if for every object x of X th=
ere
> exists an object r of A and a biuniversal arrow x -> Gr from x to G.

Of course this begs the obvious question, how hard is this to generalise =
to
bicategories?

I'm surprised no-one has mentioned Gurksi's thesis, which I just came acr=
oss.
Appendix A has details of adjunctions in bicategories, and biadjunctions =
in
tricategories, citing Verity's thesis in the case of Gray-categories.

Best,

David



